1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:05,310
Episode 25

2
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,240
You are Jang Do Hun, aren't you?

3
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:13,400
Yes, I am.

4
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:17,580
We are police officers.

5
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:26,010
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

6
00:00:28,390 --> 00:00:34,490
Conductor, one year ago, were  you there with me in that warehouse?

7
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:42,370
Is that your knife?

8
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:53,500
What are you doing here, without my knowledge?

9
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:56,600
Please answer my questions first.

10
00:00:59,190 --> 00:01:02,110
Jang Yun left this here.

11
00:01:02,110 --> 00:01:03,420
Yun did that?

12
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:07,900
As he handed this to me, he asked the same question, "Is this your knife?"

13
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:12,600
- Why did Yun ask you that question?
- I don't know either.

14
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:16,550
Suddenly I felt what does he mean and  that was obnoxious.

15
00:01:16,550 --> 00:01:19,800
- It seemed there was some kind of misunderstanding.
- A misunderstanding?

16
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:25,060
Someone must have told him that I had followed Ian's car on the day of the Asia Philharmonic concert last year.

17
00:01:25,060 --> 00:01:30,290
- Who was that?
- I have no idea. Anyway that person was mistaken.

18
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:34,920
You also know.  Because of that concert, everyone was following a tough schedule.

19
00:01:36,870 --> 00:01:40,740
I was overcome with tiredness and couldn't go to the wrap party and went straight home.

20
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:48,300
Now it's your turn. ... What are you doing here?

21
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:53,600
You know this person, don't you? He was discovered as a corpse yesterday.

22
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,500
You've met him before, haven't you?

23
00:01:58,620 --> 00:02:02,230
- I have seen him before.
- When?

24
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:05,810
Last year. He committed a hit-and-run and killed my younger brother.

25
00:02:05,810 --> 00:02:08,100
I saw him from far away at the last hearing of his trial.

26
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,440
But you haven't met him recently?

27
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:13,450
Why would you ask me that?

28
00:02:13,450 --> 00:02:15,670
We will have to investigate further to be sure

29
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:20,230
but all the people who've met with Yun Yeong Gil after he was released from prison are all involved with that accident a year ago.

30
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:22,300
Such as yourself.

31
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:25,900
You are the older brother of Kim Ian, who died, and you also work at Sinyeong Philharmonic.

32
00:02:25,930 --> 00:02:28,900
And you have plenty of motive.

33
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:32,900
Are you sure you haven't met with Yun Yeong Gil recently?

34
00:02:36,410 --> 00:02:41,390
I don't know why you keep asking me this.

35
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:46,950
This person would not know that I was Ian's older brother.

36
00:02:46,950 --> 00:02:52,610
Unless he knew us when we were young, there is no way for him to know that we were brothers.

37
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:57,220
There is no connection. We have different last names and we are listed on different family registers.

38
00:02:57,300 --> 00:03:00,500
The attorney who represented Ian's interests was hired by our mother.

39
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,690
So how would this man know to contact me?

40
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:09,350
Even if he did contact me, why do you think I would agree to meet him?

41
00:03:10,730 --> 00:03:13,370
So you are saying you didn't meet with him?

42
00:03:13,370 --> 00:03:16,710
I'm saying the question itself is offensive.

43
00:03:25,050 --> 00:03:27,590
Why won't you answer?

44
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:31,590
Is there some reason you don't want to tell me why you came here?

45
00:03:42,110 --> 00:03:44,700
No.

46
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:49,600
I was just curious about something, and wanted to confirm something I saw.

47
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,500
So what did you see?

48
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:56,400
I found flowers in your office.

49
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:10,290
I received so many flowers, so I wouldn't know. Also, it was not given to me directly.

50
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:17,700
The day of that incident, Kim Ian and I

51
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:24,100
were locked in a warehouse, and someone came in.

52
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,820
I picked up the knife that he dropped.

53
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:43,720
If you come near me, I will stab you, so go away!

54
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:48,150
and I stabbed Kim Ian with that knife.

55
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:57,600
I can't remember much after that.

56
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,500
Some man chased me

57
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:08,090
and the person who chased me at that time

58
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:13,010
was Yun Yeong Gil, who died here today.

59
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,200
So why are you telling me this?

60
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:24,300
I don't have anything to do with that incident.

61
00:05:45,610 --> 00:05:50,910
I remembered seeing you, Conductor.

62
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,400
- You saw me?
- Yes.

63
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,300
You came into the warehouse that day, didn't you?

64
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:02,300
Yun Yeong Gil told me

65
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:07,940
that besides me and Kim Ian, there was someone else in the warehouse.

66
00:06:08,790 --> 00:06:12,890
And that he could be the real culprit for Kim Ian's murder.

67
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:14,850
And that culprit is me?

68
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:17,980
I saw it and remember it clearly.

69
00:06:20,410 --> 00:06:22,160
You are mistaken.

70
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:26,470
No, I remember it accurately.

71
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:29,720
Your face was covered, but I can tell.

72
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:35,430
Couldn't you just tell me honestly what really happened that day?

73
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,680
Nothing happened, you are mistaken.

74
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,870
- Did you kill Kim Ian?
- No.

75
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:41,500
- What about Yun Yeong Gil?
- No.

76
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,990
- What did you do there?
- I didn't go to that warehouse, you are mistaken!

77
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:46,350
Please stop lying.

78
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:54,600
If you're going to treat me like a murderer, bring me the evidence.

79
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:59,970
Conductor, I adored you for seven years.

80
00:06:59,970 --> 00:07:05,950
When I was able to work by your side, you can't imagine how happy I was.

81
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:11,930
Where did the Conductor that I liked and respected go?

82
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:19,370
I would like you to leave my office now.

83
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:24,860
You think I'm a murderer, so what else do we have left to say?

84
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,630
Beethoven
Sonata in F

85
00:07:34,630 --> 00:07:37,540
I will take this.

86
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:44,130
I can no longer believe what you say.

87
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,960
Evidence?

88
00:07:47,110 --> 00:07:49,870
I will bring it to you.

89
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:07,430
I Wanna Hear Your Song

90
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:39,400
I packed up some of Ian's things and some photos. Can you keep them for me?

91
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,400
Photos of Hong Yi Yeong?

92
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:46,040
Yes, I didn't want there to be any problems, just in case there is an investigation.

93
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:48,900
Yun Yeong Gil worked part-time at Hong Yi Yeong's uncle's shop.

94
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:52,540
I'm sure the police went to question them as well.

95
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:56,460
If they find a picture or something at my home, things can get out of control.

96
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:58,950
I hope that Yi Yeong wouldn't get involved in this incident.

97
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,900
You're providing testimony as a witness?

98
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:03,100
You can refuse that.

99
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,470
It will be easier for me to just do it.

100
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,700
I think they suspect that it's a murder.

101
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:13,810
I'm sure you'll be fine

102
00:09:13,810 --> 00:09:16,050
but you have to be careful until the end.

103
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,850
Alright.

104
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:30,730
Insomnia

105
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:33,000
Yes?

106
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:52,700
Don't wander around and stay at home. Is something wrong?

107
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:59,700
I remember everything. About that night, who was at the warehouse.

108
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,830
Who?

109
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,200
The conductor.

110
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:11,100
I can't confirm it because he had a mask, but I'm sure it was him.

111
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:23,030
Did you give this knife to the conductor?

112
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:30,300
I was suspecting Nam Ju Wan as well.

113
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:33,010
On the day of the performance last year,

114
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:37,950
I heard Nam Ju Wan followed Ian's car, according to Eun Ju.

115
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:40,150
Eun Ju told you that?

116
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,570
I was wondering if she just said it because she fought with him,

117
00:10:44,570 --> 00:10:47,560
but anyway it's worth looking into.

118
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:53,100
I went to ask  him about the knife. But where did you find this?

119
00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:59,860
In the conductor's office. I just came from meeting him.

120
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:03,530
- You met him?
- Yes.

121
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:07,070
I asked him if he was in the warehouse last year, and he said he wasn't.

122
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:10,900
He said not to call him a murderer and bring evidence.

123
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,780
Evidence?

124
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:21,400
I can't believe it. Everything seems like a lie.

125
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:30,120
I feel sorry towards you at times like these,

126
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,770
but there's something I have to say to you as well.

127
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:35,780
To me?

128
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:38,320
I should not put it off any longer.

129
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,060
What is it?

130
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,930
It's about my name.

131
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:48,590
Your name?

132
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:53,590
The name you know, Jang Yun.

133
00:11:53,590 --> 00:11:58,590
That's not my name, it was my brother's. When he was young.

134
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:05,460
Then, what's your real name?

135
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:09,330
Jang Do Hun.

136
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:12,350
Jang Do Hun?

137
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:15,560
Do you remember someone named Jang Do Hun?

138
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,570
Who?

139
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:25,000
What is it that you remember? You saw him a few times in college.

140
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:29,550
Have you worked as a teacher's assistant at Sinyeong, by any chance?

141
00:12:30,290 --> 00:12:33,230
Yes. Why?

142
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:37,390
It's just that Eun Ju brought it up.

143
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:40,710
Whether I remember someone named Jang Do Hun.

144
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:43,800
I guess that means she knew something.

145
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:49,230
I'm sorry. I should've told you sooner.

146
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:52,100
I'm sorry for the bad timing.

147
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:56,950
No, it's okay. I understand.

148
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:59,670
You're not going to ask? Why I used his name?

149
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:05,100
You must have had a good reason. Your situation wasn't so great.

150
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:11,520
Ian said he told you that name,

151
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:14,090
which is also why I made that choice.

152
00:13:14,090 --> 00:13:19,520
I thought if I used that name, you might

153
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:22,590
remember my brother and everything more quickly.

154
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:29,090
It's a poor excuse. I'm sorry.

155
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:32,500
I said I understand everything.

156
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:38,970
You're not hiding anything else from me, are you? Tell me everything now.

157
00:13:38,970 --> 00:13:44,060
There's nothing. Now there's nothing I'm fooling you about.

158
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:48,410
♫ all those times ♫

159
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:52,590
♫ like this ♫

160
00:13:52,590 --> 00:13:56,430
♫ remain in you ♫

161
00:13:58,090 --> 00:14:03,040
♫ I can't hear ♫

162
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:08,010
♫ I can't see ♫

163
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:11,720
♫ that exciting day ♫

164
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,160
♫ that day ♫

165
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:16,370
I've always wanted to throw it out.

166
00:14:18,950 --> 00:14:22,130
Let's forget it now, that knife.

167
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:28,640
I don't know if it's okay for Ian, but you should forget about it now.

168
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:30,640
♫ that brilliant day ♫

169
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,160
I can't forget.

170
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:35,670
♫ that day, beautiful day ♫

171
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:39,200
I'm sure that someday the memory might fade.

172
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:43,100
♫ on that happy day, still loving you ♫

173
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:46,370
♫ to be loving you ♫

174
00:14:47,810 --> 00:14:51,650
♫ I'm gonna love with you ♫

175
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,490
Letter of Resignation

176
00:14:58,420 --> 00:15:01,760
The atmosphere isn't so good lately, so I'm sorry.

177
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:06,370
You're leaving for a good reason, don't be sorry. We should congratulate you.

178
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:10,840
You are my senior, so please speak casually.

179
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,760
Should I?
(informally)

180
00:15:13,890 --> 00:15:18,220
CEO Jang made a good choice. You should be thankful.

181
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:20,660
But how did you know him?

182
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:25,640
I sought him out. Trying to find a way to survive, by whatever means.

183
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:30,560
I was working under Professor Kang, but some trouble came up.

184
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:34,810
He threatened to fire me.

185
00:15:37,950 --> 00:15:41,310
You should've told me.

186
00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:44,920
- You're not on our side.
- Your side?

187
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:50,800
If Professor Kang and I are both drowning, who would you rescue?

188
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:55,730
I always thought you were on his side.

189
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:04,540
I want to see you fly high. I'm being sincere.

190
00:16:04,540 --> 00:16:08,470
If you need it, you can use the individual practice room. I'll look the other way.

191
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:10,770
Just tell me beforehand.

192
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:13,620
Thank you.

193
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:27,700
Director, detectives are here to see the Conductor.

194
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:33,760
The conductor?  Alright. The President left, right? Take them to his office.

195
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,330
Yes, ma'am. Wait, but...

196
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:39,720
I think I made a mistake.

197
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,860
What mistake?

198
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:43,310
About the person who died yesterday,

199
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:48,110
the detectives talked about flowers so, without realizing ...

200
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:54,100
I mentioned that someone went to the conductor's room with flowers.

201
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:58,100
- There was such a person?
- Yes.

202
00:16:59,370 --> 00:17:04,990
Alright. Tell the orchestra members that rehearsal will be postponed today and ask for their understanding.

203
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:10,840
Assistant Yang, you can never tell the musicians about this.

204
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:12,430
Understand?

205
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,250
Yes.

206
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:26,480
What do you need to ask me?

207
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,410
Yun Yeong Gil who died here yesterday

208
00:17:28,410 --> 00:17:31,640
brought flowers to your room, we were told.

209
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:32,770
Really?

210
00:17:32,770 --> 00:17:37,310
Have you ever met Yun Yeong Gil?

211
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:42,410
- No. And I didn't receive the flowers directly.
- Did you know Yun Yeong Gil from before?

212
00:17:42,410 --> 00:17:45,050
I don't know him personally.

213
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:48,600
But, you do know him, correct?

214
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:53,440
I have received flowers from him a few times when I was at Asia Philharmonic.

215
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,900
So I remember his name.

216
00:17:57,830 --> 00:18:00,160
What did you do with the flowers you received?

217
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,540
I threw them out, because they withered.

218
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:06,790
I understand. If we ever need you, we can call you in as a witness, right?

219
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:08,750
Of course.

220
00:18:15,490 --> 00:18:17,710
Let's talk.

221
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:24,560
- What do you want?
- Should I share the fact that you met Yun Yeong Gil?

222
00:18:40,190 --> 00:18:42,350
What do you want?

223
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:48,370
I was following you yesterday, when I saw you meet with Professor Kang.

224
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:52,050
Now you're stalking me as well. So what?

225
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:57,300
I even took photos and recorded you. It was quite a conversation you two had.

226
00:18:57,300 --> 00:19:01,900
Someone died, and you were blaming each other, that was quite something.

227
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:05,900
I really couldn't even stand to watch it.

228
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:09,430
So?

229
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:11,750
Did Professor Kang kill my brother?

230
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:17,050
That's what you told him. Killed not one but two people.

231
00:19:17,050 --> 00:19:19,830
You should ask Professor Kang.

232
00:19:19,830 --> 00:19:23,470
Of course, you wouldn't answer. Right.

233
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:29,660
I really cannot understand you.

234
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:32,870
But you know about that night. You were at the warehouse.

235
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:36,170
But why didn't you say anything? For what reason?

236
00:19:36,170 --> 00:19:39,790
You said Ian was a precious junior. He was your only friend, you said.

237
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:42,360
There's something more important than that, which you want to keep hidden?

238
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:44,090
What would you know?

239
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:48,420
You grew up with a silver spoon in your mouth, getting anything you wanted.

240
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:53,590
You and I are different.  I couldn't have anything unless I struggled for it.

241
00:19:53,590 --> 00:20:00,050
Do you know how much willpower and how much hard work it took for me to get this position?

242
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:05,730
There is no one in this world who gets everything they want. Everyone is like you.

243
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:10,200
Are they really? How easy it is to say that.

244
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:15,210
Have you ever thought about selling your organs because you were desperate for funds to study abroad?

245
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:17,700
You haven't.

246
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:26,750
I'm not someone who wants love. I want to be in this position and receive respect.

247
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:30,860
For this, I exerted myself to the point of death, and I'm still doing it.

248
00:20:30,860 --> 00:20:36,490
Do you know what I fear more than death? Falling behind and being pushed down.

249
00:20:36,490 --> 00:20:40,890
I've finally arrived at this position.

250
00:20:40,890 --> 00:20:47,050
I don't want to take even one step down. Is that such a sin?

251
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:50,590
So do you think you can receive respect right now?

252
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:56,550
At the very least, you aided and abetted murder, or you committed manslaughter.

253
00:20:56,550 --> 00:20:57,990
If you don't know anything, get out.

254
00:20:57,990 --> 00:21:02,190
I will keep asking you and chasing you, until I collapse from exhaustion.

255
00:21:02,190 --> 00:21:06,660
Until you say with your own mouth all the things you did.

256
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:29,050
So do you think you can receive respect right now?

257
00:21:29,050 --> 00:21:33,430
At the very least, you aided and abetted murder, or you committed manslaughter.

258
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:46,370
Conductor, do well.

259
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:51,130
Today will be your last performance.

260
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:28,560
It seems you've already changed your mind?

261
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:33,030
I knew you are very smart.

262
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:36,770
How much? Where do I send it?

263
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:41,610
You already know where I receive my money.

264
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:45,020
Don't put your hands on me.

265
00:22:46,900 --> 00:22:50,330
Why not? Am I dirty?

266
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:54,770
Aren't you people even dirtier than I am?

267
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:58,520
Do you really think that?

268
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:04,000
You live like a parasite, cleaning up after others.

269
00:23:07,390 --> 00:23:10,570
Conductor, you see,

270
00:23:10,570 --> 00:23:13,980
I at least know I'm a bad guy.

271
00:23:13,980 --> 00:23:18,790
You do all sorts of dirty deeds, and even kill people,

272
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:25,160
but you don't even consider for one moment that you might be bad.

273
00:23:26,570 --> 00:23:28,800
Am I wrong?

274
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:34,500
Let's be clear about this, who killed anyone?

275
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:43,460
You think that there were no witnesses to Kim Ian's death last year, don't you?

276
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:46,370
The world has changed, Conductor.

277
00:23:46,370 --> 00:23:50,210
Why do you think only people can see?

278
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:54,000
What are you saying?

279
00:23:55,460 --> 00:24:02,050
Here's a hint. I think you also need the thing that I've hidden.

280
00:24:03,470 --> 00:24:05,950
If I need it, I will tell you.

281
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:16,910
Why? Leaving already? About to go conduct?

282
00:24:16,910 --> 00:24:19,910
The performance is starting, get out of my way.

283
00:24:21,850 --> 00:24:25,870
So go do your conducting, which is supposedly so great.

284
00:24:25,870 --> 00:24:29,720
I'm sure you will feel it down to your bones today

285
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:33,780
whether you truly deserve to be there or not.

286
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:35,960
Got it?

287
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:42,300
How dare you talk about who deserves what?

288
00:25:41,850 --> 00:25:45,280
Make it quick, I don't enjoy sitting with you.

289
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:49,440
You knew who Jang Do Hun was, didn't you?

290
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:53,150
You knew it all. You should have told me.

291
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:57,700
Why should I? I don't even like talking to you.

292
00:26:00,190 --> 00:26:05,100
Do you remember anything particular about him?

293
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:09,360
I was trying to recall any lectures, even, but I just can't remember.

294
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:14,220
I don't remember much, either. He was a very ordinary teaching assistant.

295
00:26:15,460 --> 00:26:17,440
We're done here, right?

296
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:23,020
You... you have loved the Conductor for a long time, haven't you?

297
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:25,400
What about it?

298
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:30,150
You once said the Conductor was even capable of killing someone.

299
00:26:30,150 --> 00:26:33,770
Did you say that because you knew something?

300
00:26:33,770 --> 00:26:38,210
If that's true, can you tell me about it?

301
00:26:38,210 --> 00:26:41,110
I told Jang Yun everything I know.

302
00:26:41,110 --> 00:26:46,290
That the Conductor followed you and Kim Ian by car last year.

303
00:26:46,290 --> 00:26:51,050
But why do you ask about that?

304
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:57,270
Did you remember the Conductor or something?

305
00:26:59,410 --> 00:27:01,450
It's not like that.

306
00:27:15,140 --> 00:27:18,030
Welcome. Planning to sleep or rest?

307
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:23,700
It's not that... this man was staying here, wasn't he?

308
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:27,610
Are you a detective?

309
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:33,200
No, I'm family, his younger brother. I wanted to take his things home.

310
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:40,370
So the investigation is over?

311
00:27:40,370 --> 00:27:44,630
Yes, yes, they came twice and went through everything.

312
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:40,860
Receipt for 50,000 won at Nebo Storage

313
00:28:45,030 --> 00:28:48,450
Yun Yeong Gil.

314
00:28:48,450 --> 00:28:51,290
He's stored all his things in a large storage space after a move.

315
00:28:51,290 --> 00:28:55,320
And he had a bag kept in a smaller storage space, but he took that bag yesterday.

316
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:58,510
He did? When?

317
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:01,420
At 6:12 p.m.

318
00:29:01,420 --> 00:29:03,890
6:12 p.m... ?

319
00:29:03,890 --> 00:29:09,600
I'm Yun Yeong Gil's younger brother. He died yesterday, early in the morning.

320
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:15,900
How do you release people's things to others? Don't you check their ID, at least?

321
00:29:15,900 --> 00:29:17,260
There is no way we would do that.

322
00:29:17,260 --> 00:29:19,700
You have surveillance cameras that run 24 hours, don't you? Can we see that?

323
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,560
Hold on, please.

324
00:29:22,790 --> 00:29:27,270
This is the video from 6:12 - 6:15 p.m.

325
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:38,000
I'm going to the police station to provide a witness statement.

326
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:43,000
I'll contact you when I'm done. Let's have a meal together, I have something to speak to you about.

327
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:54,630
Personal Information
Name:  Jang Yun

328
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:59,600
Your name is different on the résumé from Sinyeong Philharmonic.

329
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:03,280
Is that related to Yun Yeong Gil's death?

330
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:09,160
Well, no, but as to your credibility....

331
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:12,590
it can have an effect. I'm a human being as well.

332
00:31:12,590 --> 00:31:16,360
You didn't give me a straight answer to my question yesterday.

333
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,350
So I will ask again.

334
00:31:18,350 --> 00:31:21,510
You have met Yun Yeong Gil recently, haven't you?

335
00:31:21,510 --> 00:31:25,540
Maybe on the day of the performance, or maybe before that?

336
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:27,740
- Yes, I have.
- Looks like you've changed your statement?

337
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:29,490
I never said I didn't not meet him.

338
00:31:29,490 --> 00:31:31,730
So when did you meet him?

339
00:31:32,550 --> 00:31:36,960
I don't remember the exact dates, but from time to time?

340
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:39,030
So why did you meet him?

341
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:41,170
He asked to borrow money.

342
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:45,410
He was just released from prison, so his life was difficult, he said.

343
00:31:46,300 --> 00:31:48,700
I almost burst out laughing, sorry.

344
00:31:48,700 --> 00:31:52,800
But why you? Aren't you a family member of the victim, and he is the assailant?

345
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,850
I don't know. It doesn't seem that anyone knows.

346
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:59,510
Yes, there are all sorts of people in the world.

347
00:31:59,510 --> 00:32:00,660
So?

348
00:32:00,660 --> 00:32:02,160
How many times did you lend him money?

349
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:06,840
He wouldn't stop asking and wouldn't go away, so I refused.

350
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:10,560
Where did you usually meet him?

351
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:12,900
How can I remember all that?

352
00:32:12,900 --> 00:32:16,260
The truth is that we received a report.

353
00:32:16,260 --> 00:32:18,400
A report?

354
00:32:19,060 --> 00:32:22,880
That you had a big fight with Yun Yeong Gil.

355
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:26,430
After we received that report, we got all the footage from the surveillance cameras

356
00:32:26,430 --> 00:32:29,140
near Yun Yeong Gil's living quarters.

357
00:32:34,250 --> 00:32:38,910
You two have met a few times.

358
00:32:49,660 --> 00:32:54,620
Kill me, kill me, go ahead and kill me.

359
00:33:00,030 --> 00:33:01,410
Why did you hit him?

360
00:33:01,410 --> 00:33:03,000
He cursed me out for not giving him money.

361
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:05,910
You were admitted to the hospital because someone attacked you from behind, weren't you?

362
00:33:05,910 --> 00:33:08,210
Was the attacker Yun Yeong Gil?

363
00:33:08,210 --> 00:33:10,150
I don't know, they never found who did that.

364
00:33:10,150 --> 00:33:14,730
The person who killed your brother asked you for money and even attacked you with a weapon.

365
00:33:14,730 --> 00:33:17,730
Didn't you kill him out of anger?

366
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:22,120
Detective, if you get angry, do you kill people?

367
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:28,690
If you don't have any more questions, I can leave now, right?

368
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,430
We're sorry, but

369
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:39,290
we have a warrant.

370
00:33:39,290 --> 00:33:42,190
A warrant? With what evidence?

371
00:33:42,190 --> 00:33:44,660
You are being arrested on  suspicion of Yun Yeong Gil's murder.

372
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:47,830
You have the right to remain silent, you have the right to an attorney,

373
00:33:47,830 --> 00:33:51,760
and anything you say can and will be used against you in a court of law.
